ngston]], SPL, 14 May 2005\n|average attendance =5,931\n|pattern_la1=_whitelower\n|pattern_b1=_whitestripes\n|pattern_ra1=_whitelower\n|pattern_sh1=_whitesides\n|pattern_so1=\n|leftarm1=0033FF\n|body1=0033FF\n|rightarm1=0033FF\n|shorts1=0033FF\n|socks1=0033FF\n|pattern_la2=\n|pattern_b2=_Safasc_Away\n|pattern_ra2=\n|pattern_sh2=\n|pattern_so2=_color_3_stripes_black\n|leftarm2=FFFFFF\n|body2=FFFFFF\n|rightarm2=FFFFFF\n|shorts2=FFFFFF\n|socks2=FFFFFF\n|preevseason=[[2003\u201304 Kilmarnock F.C. season|2003\u201304]]\n|nextseason=[[2005\u201306 Kilmarnock F.C. season|2005\u201306]]\n}}\n\nThe [[2004\u201305 in Scottish football|2004\u201305 season]] was [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock's]] sixth consecutive season in the [[2004\u201305 Scottish Premier League|Scottish Premier League]], having competed in it since its inauguration in [[1998\u201399 Scottish Premier League|1998\u201399]]. Kilmarnock also competed in the [[2004\u201305 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]] and the [[2004\u201305 Scottish League Cup|League Cup]].\n\n==Summary==\n\n===Season===\nKilmarnock finished seventh in the [[2004\u201305 Scottish Premier League|Scottish Premier League]] with 49 points.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.espn.in/football/table?season=2003&league=SCO.1 | title=Scottish Premiership Table 2004-05 | publisher=[[ESPN FC]] | work=espnfc.com | accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> They reached the third round of the [[Scottish League Cup|League Cup]], losing to [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Hearts]]<ref>{{cite web | url=https://gh.soccerway.com/matches/2004/09/22/scotland/league-cup/heart-of-midlothian-fc/kilmarnock-fc/223666/ | title=Hearts vs. Kilmarnock 2 - 1 | publisher=Soccerway | work=Soccerway.com | date=22 September 2004 | accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref> and the fourth round of the [[Scottish Cup]], also losing to [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Hearts]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://gh.soccerway.com/matches/2005/02/16/scotland/scottish-cup/kilmarnock-fc/heart-of-midlothian-fc/239435/?ICID=PL_MS_02 | title=Hearts vs. Kilmarnock 1 - 3 | publisher=Soccerway | work=Soccerway.com | date=16 February 2005 | accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Results and fixtures==\n{{legend2|#ccffcc|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffffcc|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffcccc|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#cccccc|Postponed|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n===Scottish Premier League===\n{{Main article|2004\u201305 Scottish Premier League}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%; text-align:center\"\n!Match!!Date!!Opponent!!Venue!!Result!!Attendance!!Scorers\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|1||7 August 2004||[[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]]||A||1\u20130||10,933|| [[Kris Boyd|Boyd]] 73\u2019\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|2||14 August 2004||[[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]||H||2\u20134||10,500||[[Gary McDonald (footballer, born 1982)|McDonald]] 14\u2019 [[Gary Wales|Wales]] 28\u2019\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|3||21 August 2004||[[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Hearts]]||A||0\u20133||11,403||\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|4||29 August 2004||[[Dunfermline F.C.|Dunfermline]]||H||1\u20130||4,854||[[Danny Invincible|Invincible]] 11\u2019\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|5||11 September 2004||[[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]]||A||2\u20130||3,106||[[David Lilley|Lilley]] 60\u2019 [[Danny Invincible|Invincible]] 72\u2019\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|6||18 September 2004||[[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]||H||0\u20131||6,686||[[James Fowler|Fowler]] 54\u2019 [[Own Goal|o.g.]] \n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|7||25 September 2004||[[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]||H||5\u20132||4,711||[[Kris Boyd|Boyd]] 7\u2019, 16\u2019, 33\u2019, 37\u2019 [[Penalty kick (association football)|(Pen.)]], 84\u2019\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|8||3 October 2004||[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]||A||0\u20132||46,278||\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|9||16 October 2004||[[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]||A||1\u20133||4,637||[[Kris Boyd|Boyd]] 5\u2019\n|-style=\"ba